FT  04 JUN 92 / Aegean leaders may meet
THE TURKISH Prime Minister, Mr Suleyman Demirel, and his Greek counterpart,
Mr Constantine Mitsotakis, are likely to meet in Istanbul this month during
a private visit by the Greek leader, a Turkish official said yesterday,
Reuter reports from Ankara.
They may meet on June 21 during a private visit to Istanbul by Mr
Mitsotakis, a foreign ministry spokesman said.
The Greek premier is also expected to meet Turkish leaders on June 25, when
10 regional leaders are to convene in Istanbul for a summit of the Black Sea
Economic Co-operation project.
Ankara and Athens are under pressure from the United Nations to help
facilitate an agreement by the Turks and Greeks of Cyprus to end the
island's partition.
